## Interface: 120005, 120001
## Title: FluentWoW
## Notes: WinUI-inspired, token-driven UI framework for World of Warcraft addon developers.
## Version: 1.5.0
## Author: Weischbier
## X-Category: Library
## X-License: MIT
## X-Website: https://github.com/TheSaltySeagull/FluentWoW
## X-Curse-Project-ID: 000000
## X-Wago-ID: PLACEHOLDER
## X-WoWI-ID: 00000
## DefaultState: enabled
## LoadOnDemand: 0

# ── Vendored libraries (load before everything) ──────────────
Libs/LibStub/LibStub.lua

# ── Core runtime ──────────────────────────────────────────────
Core/Bootstrap.lua
Core/Utils.lua
Core/EventBus.lua
Core/StateMachine.lua
Core/FramePool.lua

# ── Token / theme system ──────────────────────────────────────
Tokens/Registry.lua
Tokens/DarkTheme.lua
Tokens/LightTheme.lua

# ── Assets (icon maps, font references) ──────────────────────
Assets/FluentIcons.lua

# ── Base control mixin ────────────────────────────────────────
Controls/Base/ControlBase.lua

# ── Motion engine (flux-derived tweening) ─────────────────────
Motion/Motion.lua

# ── Controls (XML template before Lua behaviour) ──────────────
Controls/MainFrame/MainFrame.xml
Controls/MainFrame/MainFrame.lua
